description.narrative: By 2022, Dominican society will be aware of and mobilized in favour of children's rights, especially of girls., which contributes to Corporate External Relations And Partnerships, Communication And Resource Mobilization, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Private Sector Engagement, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022 the most vulnerable children and adolescents, and especially girls, will have access to public policies and programmes that promote social inclusion and are supported by Dominican society

description.narrative: UNICEF has sensitized and mobilized Dominican society through: a) public advocacy and communication campaigns, such as the one that sought f public support for the passing of the new legislation proposal that prohibits child marriage, b) the creation of platforms for the participation of adolescents as agents of change, who prepared the Adolescents´ Manifesto, read it in the media and presented it to the Vice President, and c) the strengthening of the commitment of a greater number of businesses, with 132 companies involved, some of which technically supported more UNICEF programmes, while others improved family-friendly policies and financed programme. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/02/2020
